State v. Frank Wilkins. (December 12, 1930.)

Pennewill, C. J., Harrington and Richards, J. J., sitting.

Reuben Sattertwaite, Attorney-General, Charles F. Richards and David J. Reinhardt, Jr., Deputy Attorneys-General, for the State. William Prickett for the defendant. Court of Oyer and Terminer for New Castle County. No. 51, May Term, 1930. *408Pennewill, C. J.,

delivering the opinion of the court:

Rape is a felony (section 4706, Revised Code of 1915), but because of the proviso as to capital cases in section 4827 of the Code, and above referred to, the motion for a new trial is refused.
